 of Marilyn Monroe, Elvis Presley, John F. Kennedy, and John Lennon. Talking to Larry King, Dion said \"It feels like when Kennedy died, when Elvis died. It's an amazing loss.\"\nA Yorkshire businessman who was working with Jackson on a proposed future project said \"I didn't think he would go out in these circumstances. It's not the way I would have expected him to go at all. He's going to become a Marilyn Monroe or an Elvis Presley.\""}
