wn with the H1N1 flu, as confirmed through testing, and there have been over 300 registered deaths attributable to the virus.\nMargaret Chan, WHO spokesperson said, \"As we see today, with well over 100 countries reporting cases, once a fully fit pandemic virus emerges, its further international spread is unstoppable.\" This sentiment has been repeated by the United Nations health official. \nThe UK health secretary, Andy Burnham has forecast over 100,000 H1N1 flu virus cases per day before September 1."}
